# piia-engram publish allowlist (WHITELIST, not blacklist)
#
# This file defines EXACTLY what is allowed to exist in the public,
# pushed repository. The CI check (scripts/check_publish_allowlist.py,
# run by .github/workflows/guard-strategic-files.yml) FAILS if any
# git-tracked file is NOT matched by an entry here.
#
# Philosophy: default-deny. Anything not explicitly allowed is assumed
# private until a maintainer consciously adds it. This is the inverse of
# .gitignore/.guardignore (which list what to keep OUT).
#
# Syntax:
#   - one path or glob per line, relative to repo root
#   - a trailing "/**" allows a whole subtree
#   - "#" starts a comment; blank lines ignored
#   - matching uses fnmatch + path-prefix semantics
#
# DEV-DOC REVIEW GATE: docs/ entries are enumerated individually on
# purpose. A new docs/*.md file will FAIL CI until a maintainer adds it
# here — that addition is the review checkpoint where you confirm the
# doc carries no reverse-disclosure (release-playbook.md §1.3/§1.4).

# ── Package source + test suite ─────────────────────────────────────
src/**
tests/**

# ── Public helper scripts (sanitize check, hook installer, etc.) ─────
scripts/**

# ── Release-gate evidence (tracked so CI can enforce it) ─────────────
release-evidence/**

# ── CI / automation ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
.github/**

# ── MCP / plugin manifests ──────────────────────────────────────────
.mcp/**
.mcp.json
.claude-plugin/**
.cursor-plugin/**

# ── Root config & build metadata ────────────────────────────────────
pyproject.toml
MANIFEST.in
.gitignore
.coveragerc
Dockerfile
glama.json
glama.yaml
smithery.yaml
install.sh
install.ps1
.publishallow

# ── Legal / governance ──────────────────────────────────────────────
LICENSE
NOTICE
SECURITY.md
PRIVACY.md
CONTRIBUTING.md
CHANGELOG.md
CHANGELOG.zh-CN.md

# ── Top-level README (bilingual) ────────────────────────────────────
README.md
README.zh-CN.md

# ── User-facing docs (ENUMERATED — see dev-doc review gate above) ────
